children.subject:
None of these classes are too hard or too much workload, so it should be quite manageable. The only thing to watch out for is all three classes are project based, so you need to balance out your time, especially if project due dates for different classes come close to each other. If possible, I would recommend trying to get a pset based class to replace one of them.

I haven't taken 169, but I think taking it helps with getting internships and doing them, but it's not necessary at all, and if you would rather take more classes, many things in 169 you would learn in an internship anyway.
